<br>
Scout in Stonebrunt Mountains<br>
<br>
The Spirit is a large blue Whisp, which spawns above the waterfall. It hits for 225 max, and procs a stun spell, for a stun of about 10 to 15 seconds. It's immune to Slow spells.<br>
<br>
Notes: stand with back to mountain as his stun is also a knockback which will push you off the mountain. Should be easy, much like the spider in LF.<br>
<br>
Scout in Permafrost<br>
<br>
A large Icebear spawns in the Pits inside Permafrost, named &quot;Icebound Spirit&quot;. He is level 55, has high Cold Resistance, but low Fire Resistance. He is immune to Slow spells, and will flurry. He hits for 225 damage maximum. Has a lot of hitpoints.<br>
<br>
Notes: This is the hardest of the scouts, need a group capable of clearing pit of bears as that is where the Spirit spawns, right in the bear pit. Also we need to make sure no one is camping bears as it is a nasty suprise for them <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
Has LOTS of hp, need at least 2 clerics, a high lvl tank and other assorted peeps. The BL turns in the token and must either A: get a CoTH to the pit, or B: invis and run and jump down into pit.<br>
fight is pretty straight forward, he does not cast.<br>
<br>
Timorous Deep - Battle with Draz Nurakk<br>
<br>
The BL turns in token and spawns (below)<br>
<br>
Green-con Draz Nurakk spawns in the small ruin on the opposite isle. When killed he will drop nothing. But when killed, this happens:<br>
<br>
Draz Nurakk's corpse explodes into thousands of brilliant glass fragments! '<br>
<br>
On his death 6 Iksars named &quot;Draz Nurakk's Image&quot; spawn. Five of them are level 53. The sixth one is level 55. Each of these images drop &quot;Shards of Broken Glass&quot; which you combine in the pouch given by the scout.<br>
<br>
Five of the images are level 53, one is level 55. One of the level 53 can not be slowed, another one can't be snared. The level 55 is immune to mez and stun, but not to slow. He has high MR, though.<br>
<br>
The level 53 ones hit for 149 max, double attack, but not too fast. The level 55 hit for 159 or 169 max. It should also be noted after they spawn and they are not agro, they will stand in the ruins in which the gren con spawned.<br>
<br>
Notes: they can be single pulled, most posts did it with only one group, might be buged, some say only 5 spawned but others said it worked fine, they were single pulled by a 51 BL in the posts.<br>
<br>
